help:
My name is Steve. I am a bot. Beep boop.
So far, there isn't much you can do with me. However, there's a little bit.

**Affirming:**
*I love you*
If you tell me you love me, I'll let you know that I love you too!
*Am I real?*
Of course you are, and I'll tell you just that.
*Lovebomb*
I'll tell you some mushy things that everyone deserves to hear.

**Practical:**
*Notes*
This one is complicated. Use heysteve notes help to get help for it.
*Role*
Syntax: heysteve role [addremove] [role|name]. Use heysteve role by itself to get more details.
*trigs*
This command is a bit complicated, so it's best to just type heysteve trigs in order to get the information on it.
*Profile*
This one is also complicated. Send heysteve profile help for more information.

**Fun:**
*daily*
Used to get the daily 200 bucks. And then some.
*bank*
Used to see what you've collected thus far.
*flip*
I'll flip a coin.
*random [number]*
I'll generate a random number between 0 and what you put in.
*What's up?*
I'll give you a random message. Can also be typed without the question mark or apostrophe.
*You're gay/You're cute/You're adorable*
Go ahead, just say it! ;)
*vore*
Just uh... Do it.

trigshelp:
**__TRIGGERS__**
Useage: heysteve trigs [set/reset/remove/add/view/new] [code/name] [trigger-flag,trigger,two|wordTrigger]

***Commands***

**Set**
*This one overwrites all currently indexed triggers. Be careful with it!*
arguments: [code] [trigger-b,two|words-w]
You may add a -b,-o, or -w for Bad, Okay, and Warn categories on this command as well as Add.
IE: heysteve trigs set 4555 icecream-o,the|color|red-b

**Add**
*This command adds to already indexed lists.*
Example: heysteve trigs add 4555 icecream-o,the|color|red-b

**Remove**
*This command removes selected triggers from whichever category/categories they're found in.*
Example: heysteve trigs remove 4555 icecream,the|color|red

**Reset**
*This command just resets everything back to none.*
Useage: heysteve trigs reset [code]

**View**
*This allows you to see your triggers or someone else's*
Useage: heysteve trigs view [code]

**New**
*This creates a new trigger list with a new code.*
Example: heysteve trigs new Jeff


**Remember that there should be no spaces between the lists. To separate, add only commas, without spaces. Spaces MUST be replaced with pipe indicators (|). Also, if you need a dash in your trigger, use an underscore (_) instead.
Also, codes are found on a user's profile under trigger codes. Use those to view/etc someone else's trigger lists. __You cannot edit someone else's lists.__**
rolehelp:
Role useage:
heysteve role [add/remove/list] [comma,separated,role|to|add]
Please note that in roles with multiple words, place a pipe indicator(|) where the space(s) should be.
IE: role name='two words' input='two|words'
You can add or remove several roles by putting a comma between them, but NO SPACES!
pfhelp:
**Profiles**

**Useage:**
heysteve profile [@ person]
Views your/the person @d's profile.
Using heysteve profile alone will offer a menu to edit your profile.
noteshelp:
Syntax: heysteve notes [add/remove/view/list/edit]

**ADD**
heysteve notes add title:title|here Body of the note
If you want a title, put 'title:' and (without spaces!) the title. If there are spaces in the title, put a | where they should be. If there isn't a title, it'll be called untitled, and if a note with that title already exists, a number will be added on!
If you want line breaks, add in a backslash (\\) where it should go.

**REMOVE**
heysteve notes remove title
Nothing too special about this, syntax is simple.

**LIST**
heysteve notes list
Lists the titles of your notes.

**VIEW**
heysteve notes view title|here
Remember to put a | for spaces if there is a space in the title!

**EDIT**
heysteve notes edit [note|title] new body here
So far, you can only overwrite the body; soon I hope to add in a text replace feature!
strikeshelp:
Syntax: heysteve * strikes [add/remove/set] [mention or number] [mention or number]
If no middle number is given on add or remove, it'll be 1 by default. A number is only needed when using 'set' and can come before or after the mention.
